Article: Weekly applications for US jobless benefits fall to the lowest level in 4 months
Summary: "The number of Americans applying for unemployment benefits fell to their lowest level in four months last week. Jobless claims slid by 12,000, to 219,000, for the week of Sept. 14, the Labor Department reported Thursday."
